posts.name: Bizzarro Italian Cafe
posts.note: Bizzarro Italian Cafe is a lively, long-running Italian eatery serving trattoria fare in a funky space with eclectic decor. The items to order are the pasta and seafood or the elk in ravioli.

posts.name: Dong Thap Noodles
posts.note: Dong Thap Noodles makes fresh in house noodles that are prepared every morning. Pho noodles, Udon, Bun Bo, Pad Thai, Thin Vermicelli noodles are made fresh daily from scratch. They are the home of the Pho Super Bowl Challenge.

posts.name: Fair Start Restaurant
posts.note: Fair Start Restaurant serves lunch and occasional dinners as part of a work training program for the homeless.

posts.name: Ivar's Seafood Restaurant
posts.note: Ivar's Seafood Restaurant is a local chain dishing up fried fish and chowders in casual quarters with nautical accents and this one s located in the Seattle-Tacoma International Airport.

posts.name: Kizuki Ramen & Izakaya
posts.note: Kizuki Ramen and Izakaya is a hip ramen shop is a local branch of a Tokyo chain, with modern steel-and-wood surrounds.

posts.name: Maneki
posts.note: Maneki is a landmark Japanese spot dating back to 1904 with tatami rooms, a bar and classic fare including sushi.

posts.name: Marination Station
posts.note: Marination Station is a cool Hawaiian-Korean spot doling out tacos, sliders, and kimchi rice bowls.

posts.name: Mee Sum Pastry
posts.note: Mee Sum Pastry is a no-frills food stand offering buns, pastries and other Chinese grub in digs by the Pike Place Market.

posts.name: Melrose Market
posts.note: Situated at the west end of the Pike-Pine neighborhood, Melrose Market is an indoor food and retail market on Capitol Hill in Seattle. It occupies a set of historic automotive buildings constructed between 1919 and 1926, which were ultimately converted into the Melrose Market.

posts.name: Pike Place Market
posts.note: Pike Place Market is a public market overlooking the Elliott Bay waterfront in Seattle, Washington, United States. The Market opened August 17, 1907, and is one of the oldest continuously operated public farmers' markets in the United States.

posts.name: Paseo Caribbean Restaurant
posts.note: Paseo Caribbean Restaurant is counter-service Caribbean joint serving sandwiches and entrees in a simple setting. The item to order is the pork sandwich.

posts.name: Quinn's Pub
posts.note: Quinn's Pub is a hip gastropub for artisanal eats & a curated beer selection in a renovated bi-level storefront.

posts.name: Rainier Restaurant and BBQ
posts.add1: 6400 Martin Luther King Jr Way S
posts.note: Rainier Restaurant and BBQ serves homestyle Vietnamese cooking is offered in a simple setting with an adjacent deli serving banh mi.

posts.name: Salumi
posts.note: Salumi is a tiny storefront offering artisanal Italian cured meats in sandwiches and by the pound. Salumi is owned and operated by Mario Batali's father. NOTE: Last time I was there they closed when they ran out of bread, but things could have changed it's been a few years.

posts.name: Sea Breeze Farms - La Boucherie
posts.note: Sea Breeze Farms - La Boucherie is a rural destination offering farm-to-table dinners from seasonal ingredients in a cozy environment.

posts.name: Seatown Seabar
posts.note: Seatown Seabar is a eat-in deli at Pike Place Market with seafood, sandwiches & rotisserie meats, plus an outdoor patio.

posts.name: Shorty's
posts.note: Shorty's is a bit of dive bar that is Coney Island-themed and a favorite hangout, offering hot dogs, nachos, pinball, and arcade games.

posts.name: The Walrus and the Carpenter
posts.note: The Walrus and the Carpenter serves oysters and other seafood plus American plates along with specialty cocktails in a small, simple space.
